2 unit(s) Beyond Meat®
4 tbsp Italian Breadcrumbs
2 unit(s) Garlic, cloves
2 unit(s) Artisan Bun
2 unit(s) Tomato
56 g Spring Mix
½ unit(s) Lemon
¼ cup Feta Cheese, crumbled
1 tsp Dill-Garlic Spice Blend
1 unit(s) Sour Cream
1 unit(s) Mini Cucumber
1 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Finely chop cucumber in 1/8-inch pieces.
Slice one tomato. Cut other tomato into 1/4-inch pieces.
Peel, then mince or grate garlic.
Zest lemon. Juice half lemon into a large bowl.
Add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil to the large bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then whisk to combine.
Add half the cucumber, diced tomato and half the spring mix to the bowl with lemon dressing.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium heat. When hot, add 1/2 tbsp oil, then Beyond Meat® patties. Pan-fry until patties are cooked through, 5-6 min per side.** (NOTE: Don't overcrowd the pan; cook patties in 2 batches for 4 ppl, using 1/2 tbsp oil per batch.)

Meanwhile, add remaininig cucumber, remaining Dill-Garlic Spice Blend, lemon zest and sour cream to a small bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine. Set aside.

Meanwhile, halve buns.
Arrange on an unlined baking sheet, cut-side up. Broil in the middle of the oven until golden-brown, 1-2 min. (TIP: Keep an eye on buns so they don't burn.)

Toss salad.
Spread tzatziki bewtween buns.
Stack sliced tomatoes, patties and spring mix on bottom buns. Close with top buns.
Divide Beyond Meat® burgers and salad between plates.
Top salad with remaining feta.

If you've opted to get Beyond Meat®, skip the instructions to form the patties.

Cook Beyond Meat® patties it the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the turkey.**